# Profile landing conventions

- Vite + Alpine.js + [vite-plugin-handlebars](https://www.npmjs.com/package/vite-plugin-handlebars) + split CSS. No backend. Publish `dist/` via GitHub Actions.
- Content: `src/data/profile.js`. Prefer editing that file for copy and links.
- Sections: `src/partials/<name>.html`, included from `index.html` as `{{> name }}`.
- i18n locales: `src/i18n/locales/` (`ru` `en` `es` `de` `zh`). Spoken langs in `profile.spokenLanguages`.
- Styles: keep section files under `src/styles/`; entry is `index.css`.
- Follow `DESIGN.md`: Steam dark palette, Exo 2 + Source Sans 3.
- Default UI language is Russian; `document.documentElement.lang` follows the switcher.
- `vite.config.js` `base` must match the Pages path (`/profile/` for this repo).
- Do not commit `node_modules/` or `dist/`.
- Versioning: keep `package.json` `version` and `CHANGELOG.md` in sync (SemVer / Keep a Changelog). See `AGENTS.md`.
- Preserve accessibility (skip link, focus-visible, reduced motion, x-cloak).
- Do not use Handlebars `{{ }}` for Alpine text binding — keep `x-text` / `:attr`.
